<p>&nbsp;Creating a digital business card with EBC is simple and requires no technical expertise. Users can choose from more than 100 professionally designed templates that suit a wide variety of industries and professions, including flower shops, travel agencies, makeup artists, chefs, developers, lawyers, doctors, spas, interior designers, gyms, architects, yoga instructors, taxi services, restaurants, schools, photographers, musicians, YouTubers, influencers, and many more. Every template is designed to be modern, visually appealing, fully responsive, and optimized for mobile devices. Users can personalize layouts, colors, branding, and other design elements without writing any code. The platform also supports both light and dark display modes, allowing users to create a digital identity that reflects their personal style or business brand.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Once a digital business card is created, it can be shared instantly through multiple channels. Contacts can access the card by scanning a QR code, tapping an NFC-enabled card, or opening a unique link. The card contains important business information such as contact details, social media profiles, image galleries, services, payment options, business hours, appointment scheduling, testimonials, and much more. Prospective clients can call directly by tapping the phone number, making communication fast and convenient. Cards can also be shared through SMS, email, messaging apps, and other online platforms, making networking easier regardless of location.</p>
<p>&nbsp;EBC goes beyond standard digital business cards by offering a complete collection of business tools. Users can create professional mobile-friendly vCards that include contact information, social media links, image galleries, services, and additional business details within a single shareable profile. The platform also allows businesses to create WhatsApp stores where products can be displayed, customer orders can be received through WhatsApp, and simple product catalogs can be managed without the complexity of traditional e-commerce systems.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Sharing options are designed to maximize accessibility and convenience. Every profile can be distributed through QR codes, NFC cards, or shortened web links. Users who purchase NFC cards can manage their card activations directly from the EBC administration panel. This combination of digital sharing methods allows businesses to connect with clients quickly while maintaining a modern and contactless networking experience.</p>
<p>&nbsp;The platform includes flexible subscription plans suitable for individuals, startups, growing businesses, and larger organizations. Users can begin with a free plan that provides essential features for creating digital business cards, managing services, products, links, payment methods, galleries, testimonials, business hours, appointments, contact forms, enquiries, password protection, and a basic online store. Paid plans significantly expand these limits by offering additional business cards, unlimited services and products, larger storage capacity, custom domains, personalized links, progressive web app functionality, advanced settings, branding removal, free setup assistance, and customer support. Higher-tier plans are designed for businesses that require unlimited digital business cards, unlimited stores, unlimited storage, and unrestricted access to all available features.</p>
<p>&nbsp;EBC also provides powerful branding and administrative capabilities. Users can customize logos, colors, and other visual elements to strengthen their brand identity. Multi-language support allows businesses to present their digital profiles effectively across different regions and audiences. The centralized administration dashboard enables users to manage business cards, subscription plans, content, and system settings from a single location. Security features and role-based access controls help maintain safe account management while supporting organizations with multiple users.</p>
